content: As a fan of ff tactics, no regret purchasing!! Very similar to tactics ogre PSP too. I love every aspect of it. My only feedback ; setting to change view angle in battle & improve storyline. Current plot is child targeted (SPOILER: repetitive small talk & unrealistic how a vet easily entrusts a trainee). I love antiquia lost plot from KEMCO so I was expecting sthing similar, good job tho. 5star because not easy to find game like this w/o paying a lot or using emulator
Good tactic game story is good so far
Nice
Loved it, please make more games like this in the future Kemco. With better gameplay and story if possible. Nice job.
Decent game worth the pay

Pretty good game overall did not give 5 stars just due to ( IMO) too many characters in battle to manage id prefer 5 or 6 in my player lineup for battle but love the roster of character lineups) im a die hard Final Fantasy Tactics fan but all in all one of the best mobile tactic like games. Nice story as well. Sequal or prequal hopefully. One of the best KEMCO games. These people got a good knack in there RPGS. Worth praise. =)
It's a Kemko RPG, with strategy elements.
Classic betrayal to a tragic death still needs a little more of the love story to help balance things out
Its fun
I liked it reminded me fft
Fun game different paths to choose from. Has a story that somewhat reminds me of Suikoden 2, definitely worth a play through if not multiple times.

Game reminds me of Tactics Ogre in Game Boy Advance. Although it reminds me of it a little too well; The splitting storyline was nice, but the music is too repetitive and poorly looped. But for an old game (Compared to the new series with Exe Create), it is rather good.
Good game with a lot of quests to get done. Interesting story and characters. At times hard to select characters.
Goog SRPG. love it.
Great game with numerous paths to go and with, unique mechanics and it was an overall blast!
great game! reminiscent of final fantasy tactics.
great game!!

A lesser FF Tactics or the like variant. Controls work well for the most 
part. Story is interesting but the dialogue at times makes no sense. I wish 
acquiring proficiency points for skills wasn't so slow. I would have liked 
an auto battle option though I acknowledge that isn't common in these kinds 
of games. Overall I like the game.
Great game! Story is fun and engaging.
it's fun to play and very good story
Can't install this games

Playing around with control for 30min and still don't get it. Can't seem to 
get the character to attack
Good game
Awesomeness
A very good game. I really enjoy it. Make more games like this please. Thanks kemco.
I'm enjoying the story and the tactics.
Game play is fun and easy. Story pretty good too. Hope to see a second game in the future
bought. installed. keep freezing on the first screen after i press "new game" cant play and cant refund. please fix i love every game from kemco
LOVE THE GAME, JUST LIKE FINAL FANTASY TACTICS, DEVS PLEASE BRING US LEGNA 2 ALREADYYYYY,   ADD MORE MAPS TO EXPLORE AND MORE PARTY MEMBERS TO RECRUIT,
To much of the same need more options and characters, it's like playing the same level over and over again.
Payed for it: downloaded, couldn't install. Waste of time; refunded.

So far, I enjoyed this game so much. It's just like other popular tactics games like FF Tactics & Tactics Ogre. Just play it, love it & have fun. Gameplay wise it's good & the story is okay, the characters development is quite good too!
legend of ixtona is better
Great gameplay.
Good Game
Nope... That's it... 5/5
It has the basic srpg elements, but bland characters and storyline. Worth it though.
My game data is lost suddenly after rebooting my device ,please help me
I won't regret bought this game
Bought it but cannot play it. Laggy and glitch even before started! Come on u can do better than this 😫
Need more item
I am using an ASUS ZenFone and have tried to instal, for a number of times but to no avail.

I've been a huge fan of SRPG games for a long time and this one have a really disappointing story. The characters are boring, the events are cliched and predictable and many many plot holes. There are many times the conversation becomes unbearable and I find myself almost faceplanting into the wall. But, I will at least commend the developer for implementing the interesting skill tree system and the simplicity of the interface. All in all it's OK, but I quitted the game around chap 22 because of the story.
Wow

I don't know why but playing this game give me more anger than others Kemco's games. maybe the cause is the not so good plot as usual, I don't see it fascinating as other Kemco's product. The items and weapons are not abundant also. Anyway this game is not bad.

Need different camera views and option to zoom in and out as well as a job class system not just one single character even fully devloped with only one set of skills as well as a rebirthing system and multiple jobs
Good game with interesting story ...
The dialog is entertaining and the game mechanics are above par. The story is SRPG standard, but there is nothing wrong with that. Thanks for the game!

Although not as great as its' predecessor, Legna still held its own from time to time. The writing could've been more descriptive in detail and dialogue needed to be concise. Overall, it was a fine game. Keep up with the srpgs!
Not bad
This game is great
I like the Ixtona UI and graphic though
I've been trying to play numerous times but keeps crashing all the time. I couldn't even finish the tutorial.
Overall great game for the price. Skill trees are great. Few different strategies to use. 4 staaars
The tactical gameplay and story is fun and the development system is cool. It'd be cool to add more diverse classes and weaponry though

It freezes on a black screen every time i try to go to a town. I like the game and would like to play through it, but i cant take jobs or go buy new equipment. So its kind of a let down. The battles and the story works fine. Just the town issue. Please fix.
Great game... funny story line just get it won't be disappointed! !!!
I love tactics games such as this one. I feel like this one is as good or better than some similar console games I've played. Hope they continue to make these!

I couldn't get through the beginning before I was absolutely sick of this game all because of the terrible writing. I can deal with glass in almost anything, but when dialogue sounds like it was written by 15 year old kids writing a fanfiction I can't take it.
Nice game

A solid strategy game with a pretty good story. It's got some cool character builds and items to find. Honestly my only complaint is the character dialogue in the game it's kind of odd...nothing bad just an observation
The story was abearable right away. Might be good if u can get past that. I uninstalled within an hour and couldn't get a refund... So lesson learned.

After playing Legend of Ixtona, I had really high hopes for this one, but I find myself pretty disappointed so far. The story isn't bad, but everything else, from music to character development, just seems lackluster. It seems like a small thing, but not being able to customize your character in any real way is just depressing. It actually feels like the developers took a step backwards rather than forward.
Ff tactics simplified but still addicting ☺
this is good...need more like this with branch storyline diffrent endings...class change will be nice too...little longer game play is nice too since this one is very short

Not a bad game, interesting at first and sorta holds your interest on first through. I'd rate it better if the game were more challenging. "Hard mode" isn't much harder unless you purposely handicap yourself. A bit more variety for victory conditions would have been good as well. It becomes repetitive having all your allies starting together every time, always on one side of the map. Story wise it's also pretty much standard kemco level. Plot is a tiny bit better than the 2014 RPGs they made. Props for that
Started off a little slow, but when it picked up it really does. I like the game a good stroy, wish the main protagonist didn't look like a little kid.

The controls are a bit touchy (but I still prefer them over Ixtona's), the graphics are average, and the story is cliched.  The game play isn't particularly revolutionary.  All but a few levels are beatable with only minimal effort.  Overall, I would describe this as generic.  However, it managed to keep me entertained for 15 hours, and I honestly enjoyed it.  It might not be anything particularly great, but it's good enough.
Played a few other ones larger installs slightly better graphics with smother gameplay. Frame rate seems slow
Stuck at loading screen , not gonna go anywhere hope it fixed soon thks.
Story plot is good,so far it runs good,I'm a huge fan of tactics type games,but I think the graphics could use a little more work,it feels outdated.
Enjoying it tremendously. Great game so far. Thanks!
Good game

Would average 3 stars for just about average everything as nothing positive stands out, but loss of 1 star is due to replay choosing different choices doesn't significantly impact the game and proceeds the usual path, the same story played over again regardless of choices chosen.  Supposedly there are 4 endings but 3 replays all with different choices and I still end up with the 4th ending.
Need a lot more games like this
Somehow I can't save and I can't change my equip but no problem in skill screen. can you please fix this. I wanna play this game. Pleaseeee. 2 stars for now can't wait to give 5 stars

It's all boring story and hardly any action. You have to read stupid dialogue for half an hour, can't skip through, can't save. Tutorial is boring as hell. Nothing new in this game, typical story based RPG, except this one makes you read much more.
Looking forward to more Kemco SRPGs, they are getting pretty good. Can't believe how little battery this drains.
Really seems like the graphics processing stutters. The menus and cursor all respond very slowly. Is it just me?
Runs smoothly on both. Fun game, good story so far. I think I see where it's heading. Only thing I would suggest is the ability to turn the camera in battle.
Fun srpg that is well worth the purchase!
But the punctuation at the end of sentences get cut off. The characters are great and the battle system is fun. I'm looking forward to replaying the game with carryover stats.

Not too far in yet but I like it. The only problem I have is that there should be more than 1 way to view the battles because it is really easy to hit the wrong square/enemy if they are bunched together.
Omg awesome!
